---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { gearPicks } from '../../data/games';
---
<Base title="Best handheld gaming accessories to buy first — Handheld Settings Lab" description="A practical accessory buying guide for Steam Deck, ROG Ally, Legion Go, and handheld PC players."><article class="wrap article"><span class="eyebrow">Gear guide</span><h1>Best handheld gaming accessories to buy first</h1><p class="muted">Start with gear that solves real handheld problems: storage, charging, protection, and docked play. We avoid fake hands-on claims and mark shopping links clearly.</p><p class="affiliate-note">Disclosure: outbound shopping links are marked sponsored/nofollow and may become affiliate links after the tracking program is connected.</p><div class="grid cols2">{gearPicks.map(item => <div class="card gear-card"><span class="chip">{item.bestFor}</span><h2>{item.title}</h2><p>{item.verdict}</p><p><strong>Typical range:</strong> {item.price}</p><a class="btn ghost" href={item.amazonUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow sponsored">Search Amazon</a></div>)}</div><h2>Buying rule</h2><p>Buy accessories in this order: storage, power, protection, then desk/TV extras. A flashy dock is less useful if your game library does not fit or your handheld dies halfway through a trip.</p><h2>What we still need</h2><ul><li>Amazon Associates tracking ID.</li><li>Direct product picks after source-backed comparison or hands-on testing.</li><li>Separate device-specific guides for Steam Deck OLED, ROG Ally X, and Legion Go.</li></ul></article></Base>
